de.wwu.muggl.instructions.interfaces.data
Interface VariablyStackPush

All Superinterfaces:
StackPush
All Known Implementing Classes:
Dup_x2, Dup2, Dup2_x1, Dup2_x2
public interface VariablyStackPush
extends StackPush

The implementing instruction is known to push an element onto the operand stack of the currently executed frame. The actual number of pushed elements cannot be determined without analyzing the preceding code.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-11
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

getNumberOfPushedElements

int getNumberOfPushedElements(byte[] types)
Get the number of elements that will be pushed onto the stack when this instruction is executed.

Parameters:
types - The types of the elements on the stack in reversed order. Non-primitive types should be represented as -1. Types are ClassFile.T_BOOLEAN, ClassFile.T_CHAR, ClassFile.T_DOUBLE, ClassFile.T_FLOAT, ClassFile.T_INT, ClassFile.T_LONG and ClassFile.T_SHORT.
Returns:
The number of elements that will be pushed onto the stack.
